Package: circlecorR
Title: Circular Correlation Wheel Plots
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Chris", "Varghese", email = "chris.varghese@alimetry.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Armen A", "Gharibans", role = "aut"))
Description: Draws MNE-style circular "correlation wheel" plots natively in R.
    Variables are arranged around a circle, grouped and colour-tiled by
    category, and connected by curved links whose colour maps to the
    correlation coefficient. Non-significant, weak, and within-category
    correlations can be masked. Correlations can be supplied as pre-computed
    r/p matrices or computed from raw data via a thin wrapper around
    'psych::corr.test'. Categories, colours, and labels are all
    user-configurable.
